# Our Place — Project Context

Community-first social media platform with one-human-one-account verification.

## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 16 (App Router) with TypeScript
- **Database**: SQLite via `better-sqlite3` (file: `data/our-place.db`)
- **Auth**: JWT in httpOnly cookies, verification code flow
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS (indigo/purple primary palette)
- **Package manager**: npm

## File Map

### Core Libraries (`src/lib/`)
- `db.ts` — SQLite connection, schema (6 tables), indexes, seed data (12 official communities)
- `auth.ts` — `signToken`, `verifyToken`, `getAuthUser`, `generateVerificationCode`
- `types.ts` — All TypeScript interfaces (`User`, `Community`, `Post`, `Comment`, `Reaction`, etc.) and constants (`COMMUNITY_CATEGORIES`, `AVATAR_COLORS`)

### Components (`src/components/`)
- `AuthProvider.tsx` — Client-side auth context (`useAuth` hook: `user`, `loading`, `refresh`, `logout`)
- `Navbar.tsx` — Top navigation with auth-aware menu
- `PostCard.tsx` — Post display with reactions and inline comments
- `CommunityCard.tsx` — Community preview card for grid layouts
- `CreatePostForm.tsx` — Expandable post creation form

### API Routes (`src/app/api/`)
- `auth/register` — POST: create account (enforces unique email + phone + username)
- `auth/login` — POST: sign in with email or username
- `auth/verify` — POST: submit 6-digit verification code
- `auth/me` — GET: current user; DELETE: logout
- `communities` — GET: list/search/filter; POST: create community
- `communities/[id]` — GET: community detail with members
- `communities/[id]/join` — POST: join community
- `communities/[id]/leave` — POST: leave community
- `communities/[id]/posts` — GET: list posts; POST: create post
- `posts/[id]/comments` — GET: list; POST: add comment
- `posts/[id]/reactions` — POST: toggle reaction
- `feed` — GET: posts from user's joined communities

### Pages (`src/app/`)
- `/` — Landing page (redirects to `/feed` if verified)
- `/auth/register`, `/auth/login`, `/auth/verify` — Auth flow
- `/feed` — Personalized feed + sidebar with joined communities
- `/communities` — Browse/search/filter all communities
- `/communities/[slug]` — Community detail with posts and members
- `/communities/create` — Create new community form
- `/profile` — User profile with community list

## Database Tables

`users`, `communities`, `community_members`, `posts`, `comments`, `reactions`

## Conventions

- Pages needing auth redirect to `/auth/login` if not logged in, `/auth/verify` if unverified
- All API routes return JSON with `{ error: string }` on failure
- UUIDs (v4) for all primary keys
- Community lookup works by both `id` and `slug`
- Only community members can post or comment within that community
